Thirty-three Polo Teams from different states of Nigeria are participating in this year’s one-week long Jos International Polo Tournament taking Place at General Hassan Usman Katsina Polo field Jos. Vice President Jos Polo Club, Sir Fom Edward Pam disclosed this to newsmen at Jos Polo Secretariat on the on going competition. According to Pam, despite threat of insecurity, people came out in their numbers to enjoy Jos international polo tournament, a sport of it’s kind that has become a unifying factor on the Plateau. He disclosed that most of the visiting players are brothers from Islamic faith, expressing gratitude to God that despite threats of kidnapping on the roads,players still turn up to participate in the competition. Pam disclosed that a head of the start of this week long competition, the organizers of the event held meetings with neighboring communities so that they should not see influx of players from neighboring states as threats . According to him, four trouphies are up for grabs at the tournament. The trouphies, he said are among others, Governor’s cup, President Cup,Imani’s cup and one other. He added that his wish was that the best players and teams should win the trouphies that are up for take away at the end of the tournament. POLL Pam Commended Nasco Group of Companies for taking 50 percent sponsorship of the tournament and Malcomines minor metals for partly taking part of the sponsorship as well. He hoped that once lasting peace is maintained on the Plateau, more groups and companies would be willing to sponsor Jos annual Polo International tournament. Pam Promised to involve showcasing of culture in the game once Jos Polo Club management finish discussion on that with the state ministry of culture and Tourism.